<H2> MESA Graphics Library </H2>
<P>
This year we are using the Mesa graphics library, which provides an
OpenGL-like API, as the platform for the course.  This library has
been installed on all the public workstations in the Computer Sciences
department. 
<P>
<UL>
<LI> <!WA5><!WA5><!WA5><!WA5><!WA5><!WA5><!WA5><!WA5><!WA5><!WA5><A HREF = http://www.cs.utexas.edu/users/fussell/mesaintro.html> Instructions </A>
for using Mesa libraries at UTCS
<LI> Sample <!WA6><!WA6><!WA6><!WA6><!WA6><!WA6><!WA6><!WA6><!WA6><!WA6><A HREF = http://www.cs.utexas.edu/users/fussell/Makefile.dist> makefile </A> for Mesa on UTCS machines
<LI> <!WA7><!WA7><!WA7><!WA7><!WA7><!WA7><!WA7><!WA7><!WA7><!WA7><A HREF = http://www.digital.com:80/pub/doc/opengl/>
OpenGL man pages </A>
<LI> The <!WA8><!WA8><!WA8><!WA8><!WA8><!WA8><!WA8><!WA8><!WA8><!WA8><A HREF = http://www.sgi.com/Technology/openGL/glspec/glspec.html>
OpenGL Specification </A>
<LI> The <!WA9><!WA9><!WA9><!WA9><!WA9><!WA9><!WA9><!WA9><!WA9><!WA9><A HREF = http://www.ssec.wisc.edu/~brianp/Mesa.html>
